race.comment: KINGSBRAE NOLA (8) has been beaten for early speed lately, last time finishing fourth (23.87) in a Grade 5 at this track. Solid record here winning seven races. Can atone. OCCITANIE (4) has a strong winning strike-rate this journey having won four of eight starts. Was out of placings last time (24.03) at this track in a Grade 5, finishing sixth and beaten 10 lengths. Looks well placed here and among the chances. LADY RICO (7) broke from the inside draw and filled a minor placing last start, beaten only 1.5 lengths (23.79) behind He's A Bonus at this track. Expected to feature. BUNDY DAMAGE (2) is worth including.
